dcterms:description: CIFAR10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR10

dcterms:description: CIFAR100 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 different classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained classification tasks compared to CIFAR10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR100

dcterms:description: CUB200 is a dataset containing 11,788 images of 200 bird species, with annotations for each image. It is widely used for fine-grained image classification tasks.

dcterms:description: Tiny-Imagenet is a smaller version of the ImageNet dataset, containing 100,000 images across 200 classes. Each image is 64x64 pixels in size, making it suitable for training models in a more resource-constrained environment.
